# Backend Python

## Routers

- New endpoints go in the appropriate `routers/<domain>.py`, not `app.py`.
- Handlers: validate input → call service → map errors → return response.
- `tools/lint_routers.py` enforces per-file budgets; regenerate baseline only intentionally.

## Services & core

- DB access patterns live in `services/` and `core/`.
- Shared upload logic: `services/upload/`.
- Entitlements and tiers: `stages/entitlements.py`.

## Worker pipeline

- Stage modules in `stages/` — each stage is a focused unit.
- `worker.py` orchestrates; do not duplicate stage logic in routers.

## Tests

- Unit tests in `tests/test_*.py`.
- Run: `python run_tests.py unit` (fast) or `python run_tests.py tiers` for entitlement flows.
- Eval harness: `python scripts/agent/eval_loop.py --mode unit`.

## Migrations

- Add migrations only in `migrations/runtime_migrations.py`.
- Do not duplicate migration lists in `app.py`.
